#X text 547 15 Both speakers will say "hello" until one of them has heard "hello" 3 times. At that point \, the speaker that heard all of the "hello" sounds will start saying "I see you". If this is said 2 times \, the other speaker will also start saying "I see you. After both speakers have said "I see you" at least 2 times \, the speakers will play a celebratory tune and move on to the next search phase or start singing if they were the only speakers left alive;
#X text 970 15 This logic holds true for all speaker search phases;
